{
 "$schema_description": "Per-witness table for experimental/notes/l1/l1_e3_dim_syz_crux_refuted.md: the L1 E3 proof-program's crux `dim Syz <= K` (K = #{mu_k>=3} >= 3), equivalent by its own proved reduction (experimental/l1_e3_obligation_v2.md) to `E_3 <= ell-2`, tested by exact F_p reconstruction of its own Syz module on 13 co-integrated witnesses (7 from l1_prime_ell_key_lemma_refuted.md Sec1, 6 from l1_e3_law_refuted.md) plus 2 E_3=ell-2 saturator controls from l1_sigma_calculus.md. Every field is recomputed from the raw `gamma` by experimental/scripts/verify_l1_e3_dim_syz_crux.py, which this JSON mirrors verbatim (companion data, not a runtime dependency of the verifier).",
